article.headline: Hofstra 80, Delaware 66
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Loren Stokes scored 25 points to help Hofstra halt a four-game losing streak with an 80-66 victory over Delaware on Saturday. Antoine Agudio added 14 points and seven assists for the Pride (11-5, 3-4 CAA), while Aurimas Kieza and Adrian Uter each had 10 points. Harding Nana scored 19 points and grabbed 12 rebounds for the Blue Hens (7-11, 4-3). Reserve Robin Wentt added 13 points. Hofstra used an 11-0 run early to open up a double-digit lead. Kieza had a pair of 3-pointers during the spurt as the Pride took a 14-4 lead. The Blue Hens got within 47-39 early in the second half before Hofstra pulled away for good with a 16-6 run.
